 knowing that would be the end of it. Now she moved wearily, partially limping from the pain in her side that had spread through much of the right side of her body. A pointless war that had ended on nothing more than the wise words of a god, bringing nothing but death and a newfound hate between two races: that of the gods and Amazons. Lines had been defined by this war, and Sartha knew it would take much time, if not forever, for certain trusts or beliefs to be regained. Such a pointless war...::<br>
<br>
::She moved towards her hut and went inside, ignoring her wound and instead tumbling into bed so that she could rest, at least for a time. Such little rest she knew. Sartha barely ever slept, but would today:: <p>~The old days are gone. You can't live in the past, and you can't wait for the future. Now is all we have. You do the other two, you waste your life...
